news.title: China Evergrande Group expects to hit 2022 property delivery target
news.para: The company aims to deliver 300,000 units this year, after delivering 256,000 between January and November, it said in a statement, citing Hui's comments in the meeting.

news.title: Rajasthan govt made changes in building by-laws under influence of realtors: Officials
news.para: On Tuesday government had made a few changes in the building bylaws of the state. Effectively, the government has decided not to allow big buildings on smaller plots measuring up to 750 sq.m.

news.title: Government amends rules to allow extraction of sand in Goa
news.para: In addition, the applicant should either have been born and had his birth registered in Goa, or have any parent or grandparent born in Goa, to apply to the government for permission.

news.title: HC quashes Nagpur Improvement Trust land allotment to private society
news.para: Petitioner Malvi Suvarnakar Sanstha through Adv Anand Parchure, had approached the court challenging the NIT's decision to allot plot no. 8 (khasra no.538) in its layout in Manewada.

news.title: Three lakh people to pay higher property tax in Chennai
news.para: ​Officials said several buildings over the years have done reconstruction or remodelling that have not yet been assessed. This drive with the help of GIS mapping will help to achieve that.

news.title: Guwahati civic body sets January 1 deadline for payment of property tax
news.para: The GMC has asked the citizens to pay property tax dues by January 1 to avoid electricity disconnection and for this the civic body has tied up with the Assam Power distribution Company (APDCL).

news.title: Tamil Nadu government should monitor house allotment under PMAY-Gramin: HC
news.para: The petition prayed for a direction to the government authorities concerned to take action against the Ariyalur district panchayat secretary and other office-bearers for making illegal allotment of houses and misappropriations, based on petitioner's representation dated December 6, 2021.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: SC orders 165 families out to raze illegal buildings
news.para: The apex court has ordered the 165 families residing in these "towers of corruption", as Krishna Complex and Trimurti Park are called by activists, to give a written undertaking that they will shift out within six months.

news.title: Gururgram: Illegal farmhouse, three multi-storey buildings razed
news.para: District town planner (enforcement) Amit Madholia said that the colony is a zero tolerance area for any construction activity but some miscreants are carrying out illegal constructions.

news.title: Jaypee offers to finish incomplete Sports City projects in next two years
news.para: JAL had approached the court against YEIDA’s order cancelling the allotment of 1,085 hectares of land given to the developer about three years ago. The next date of hearing is December 12.

news.title: Mumbai: Industrialist Nusli Wadia looking to offload slum-encroached 20 acres
news.para: These land parcels belong to the F E Dinshaw Charities and F E Dinshaw Trust, of which Wadia is the administrator, and are heavily encroached by slums.

news.title: Supreme Court ends large tax evasion in land, property deals
news.para: No stamp duty, capital gains and income tax were paid as is required in a plain sale and transfer of property. The partnership entity, through which funds flowed in and out, let a new set of partners control the property.

news.title: President signs amendment in MHADA Act, paves way for redevelopment of cessed buildings
news.para: The President of India signed the amendments in the MHADA Act 1976, giving preference to the owner or the tenants of a residential building to submit a proposal for redevelopment once it is categorised by the civic body as dangerous for living

news.title: Give management of Amrapali Group to Uttar Pradesh govt if financial issues not resolved: Attorney General
news.para: ​Home buyers, through their counsel, submitted NBCC has completed construction of around 3,000 flats left incomplete by the Amrapali group but no electricity and water connections have been provided by the Noida and Greater Noida authorities.

news.title: Blackstone to sell stake in MGM Grand, Mandalay Bay to VICI Properties
news.para: The deal includes the assumption of Blackstone Real Estate Investment Trust's (BREIT) existing property-level debt that has a principal balance of $3 billion.
